callContract(string,string,bytes,uint8,u.details: Calls a contract on a specific destination chain with the given payload

params.destinationAddress: The address of the contract to be called on the destination chain
params.destinationChain: The target chain where the contract will be called
params.gasValue: The amount of gas to be paid for the cross-chain message. If this is 0, then gas payment is skipped. `msg.value` must be at least gasValue.
params.metadataVersion: The version of metadata to be used
params.payload: The data payload for the transaction

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the GatewayCaller contract

params.gasService_: The address of the AxelarGasService contract
params.gateway_: The address of the AxelarGateway contract
